startLevel

public boolean startLevel(int gameLevelIndex)
Starts game's level with specified index. This method interrupts currenly running game in any and start new game loop thread gameLoopThread setting game's state gameState to Game.GameState.PLAY. Level index gameLevelIndex must be in the range [0; getLevelsCount() - 1].

Parameters:
gameLevelIndex - Level's index
Returns:
true on success, false otherwise
See Also:
restartLevel(), goToPreviousLevel(), goToNextLevel(), stop(), stop(boolean), getLevelsCount()

stop

public void stop()
Stops the game if it's running. This method interrupts game loop thread gameLoopThread and changes game's state gameState to Game.GameState.STOP.

See Also:
stop(boolean), startLevel(int)

stop

public void stop(boolean switchToIntroduction)
Stops the game if it's running and switches to introduction screen in the case of switchToIntroduction is set to true. This method interrupts game loop thread gameLoopThread and changes game's state gameState to Game.GameState.STOP or Game.GameState.INTRODUCTION.

Parameters:
switchToIntroduction - Application will be switched to introduction screen if this flag is set to true
See Also:
stop(), startLevel(int)

run

public void run()
Implements game loop. This method attempts to do worker's movement if any is forced by the user with compliant methods:
  • forceWorkerToMoveLeft()
  • forceWorkerToMoveRight()
  • forceWorkerToMoveUp()
  • forceWorkerToMoveDown()
The time taken for one game loop's execution is measured by GameGraphics.getGameLoopIterationTime() in milliseconds.

Specified by:
run in interface java.lang.Runnable
